{| class="wikitable" |+ Priestess hierarchy ! Title ! Description |- ! {{nihongo||聞得大君|[[:en:Kikoe-ōgimi|Kikoe-ōgimi]]||extra=Okinawan: {{transliteration|ryu|chifi ufujin}}}} | Royal priestess, a blood relative of the king, residing in Shuri. |- ! {{transliteration|ja|Izena noro}} | Directly ruled [[:en:Izena, Okinawa|Izena]] Magiri. |- ! {{transliteration|ja|Kudaka noro}} | Directly ruled [[:en:Kudaka Island|Kudaka Island]]. |- ! {{transliteration|ja|[[Mihara-oamu-shirare]]}} | Priestesses in charge of the three [[:en:Administrative divisions of the Ryukyu Kingdom|districts]] of Kunigami, Nakagami, and Shimajiri. |- ! {{transliteration|ja|Noro}} | Village or {{transliteration|ja|[[magiri]]}} priestess. |- ! Assistants | Typically a girl representing a family in a village or a {{transliteration|ja|noro}}-in-training, but can be a man for public ceremonies. |}
